* Desmonus sighed as she touched down just outside of the Alliance base, her 
current home and where her master dwelled.
She looked over the ship and sighed again, rubbing the joints of her wings 
while she stepped towards the ship.
It hadn't been a long flight but with her hunger she was growing weak, and 
the light of this day was just too much for a vambot to take for long.
Desmonus entered into the warm confinds of the ship and looked around 
briefly, discovering the new scents and feelings things had.
But her stomach rumbled and her mind once again returned to finding a 
suitable meal, faintly wondering just whom of the Alliance crew would fall 
victom to her venilouse bite!*
